AXA Insurance Selects International Business Machines Corp for Systems Integration Project in Romania-MarketLine (a Datamonitor Company), Company News
Monday, 26 Mar 2012 06:00am EDT
MarketLine (a Datamonitor Company), Company News reported that AXA Insurance has selected International Business Machines Corp (IBM)'s smarter computing model for a four-year systems integration project in Romania designed to streamline business processes, reduce information technology costs, and uncover new business opportunities. Under the agreement signed in 2011, IBM will provide systems integration and management services to help streamline risk management, consolidate data to provide the company with a single view of customers, and work to lower operational costs by automating several pieces of the insurance process. IBM will facilitate the computing project through its data center in Petrom City. Also as part of the agreement, IBM will migrate Omniasig's client system to a centralized ERP SAP solution and standardize business-use rules across information technology applications to enable workload optimization and integration. The moves are designed to create a more open, flexible, scalable, efficient, and secure system that provides AXA Insurance Romania with visibility into, and control over, insurance policies as well as help reduce internal investment costs.Â 
